Nicole Matthiesen is a holistic healing guide, Ayurvedic health advisor, and the founder of NM Yoga + Wellness. 

After (over)working for many years in the corporate world, she found herself burnt out and experiencing chronic health issues, including IBS. Working with various modalities, from yoga and Ayurveda, to tarot and other spiritual practices, Nicole experienced profound healing in body, mind, and spirit.  

Deeply transformed by this healing journey, she left the corporate world and now supports others in healing and thriving through Ayurvedic consultations, coaching, intuitive tarot readings, and more....read more

My training concerns the visual imaging of creative positive ideas, basically anchored in the Christian Tradition, but including many connections to other traditions: Taoism and Buddhism. The presentations are consisting in relative short audio clips, no more than ten minutes, on various actual topics: depression, loneliness, anxiety, unhappiness, and so on. The basic intention is to treat all the emotional deficiencies by relating them to the great archetype of the Primordial Man that in echo will restore the balance and perfect image of any human being. Without abusing in Christian symbols, even by substituting them for universal concepts valid irrespective of culture, even for atheists, the purpose is not to convert to a specific belief, but to heal by restoring the primordial harmony, inherent for any human being at the age of childhood. 

I live in Bucharest, Romania, and I work as communications engineer in the space industry....read more

I am an online Yoga entrepreneur, and coach for deepening and advancing your practice on ALL levels -  for your Hero's Journey.

My program is: Ground to Crown - Slow Down to Power-Up Your Yoga + Spiritual Life

I have been practicing Yoga, meditation, mindfulness and the martial arts (Chinese Kung Fu - Wing Chun)  for 8 years. I would consider myself a student of mystical traditions. My interests and experiences include:

Yoga philosophy; Buddhism, Taoism, Zen; Shamanism, Sufism, Native American philosophy; Poetry from Mary Oliver, Linda Hogan, Joy Harjo, Rumi, Hafiz, etc; Christian Mysticism, Catholic Saints; Sacred Geometry; Plant Medicines, and Psychedelic healing.

Especially Joseph Campbell, the monomyth, and the ideals laid out in his book, The Hero With a Thousand Faces. 

I am impassioned by the Hero's Journey: 

Reconciling of all pairs of opposites in the heart. 
Balancing and harmonizing male and female polarity. 
Becoming aware of the purpose of life, and why you are here....read more

I’ve have always had an ancient thirst for knowledge, growing up I would experiment with exploring the deeper facets of my mind. I was born in Nepal. I’ve always been curious and have this desire to understand my roots, this has taken me on the path of self-discovery. When I visited Nepal in my mid-20s , I stayed in Ananda Yoga Centre where I worked closely with a guru who helped me establish my practice. I found that through deep meditation, I was able to discover my true essence.

I started studying stress and the effects it has on the human body quite extensively around 2012. I was very intrigued on how stress was the common denominator for disease in our community. I realised at that time that meditation was the antidote to stress in the body; this motviated me to study the relationship between mind, body and energy.

I realised that through meditation we could not only discharge stress but internally engineer a better version of ourselves, this was the inspiration for StressFit.

I’ve conducted a lot of seminars and workshops for many corporate companies such as Jenny Craig, ANL lighting, Lulu Lemon and many yoga studios. Hot Yoga Mix Point Cook is my home base of teaching meditation to my students.

I continue to grow and evolve as an universal student of consciosness on a self-discovery jounrey within the self - I AM THAT I AM....read more
